# ORICALO AI Agent Rules (.cursorrules)

## Project Overview
ORICALO is an Urdu-first AI voice agent for real estate. It uses a Monorepo structure with Next.js (Frontend) and FastAPI (Backend).

## Tech Stack
- **Frontend**: Next.js 14+ (App Router), TypeScript, Tailwind CSS, Lucide React.
- **Backend**: Python 3.10+, FastAPI, WebSockets, PyTorch, HuggingFace Transformers.
- **AI/ML**: Whisper (STT), Llama/Mistral (LLM), FAISS (RAG).

## Directory Structure
- `frontend/`: Next.js application.
- `backend/`: Python AI server.
    - `app/`: FastAPI core.
    - `stt/`: Speech-to-Text module.
    - `llm/`: LLM & Dialogue Policy.
    - `rag/`: Retrieval Augmented Generation.
    - `tts/`: Text-to-Speech.
- `training/`: Model fine-tuning scripts.

## Coding Standards

### Python (Backend)
- Follow **PEP 8**.
- Use Type Hints (`typing.List`, `typing.Optional`, etc.).
- Use `pydantic` for data validation.
- Docstrings for all public functions/classes (Google style).
- **Async/Await**: Use `async def` for I/O bound operations (DB, Network).

### TypeScript/React (Frontend)
- Use **Functional Components**.
- Use `interface` for props.
- **Tailwind CSS** for styling (no CSS modules unless necessary).
- Use `lucide-react` for icons.
- **Strict Mode**: Ensure no `any` types if possible.

## Agentic Behaviors
- **Plan First**: Before writing complex code, create/update `implementation_plan.md`.
- **Atomic Changes**: Keep changes focused. Don't refactor unrelated code.
- **Verify**: Always check if the code compiles/runs after changes.
- **Urdu Support**: Ensure UI supports RTL (Right-to-Left) text where appropriate (though primary UI might be English for admins, Urdu for content).

## Specific Rules
- **Streaming**: Prioritize low-latency streaming for Audio/STT. Use WebSockets.
- **Environment**: Use `.env` files for secrets. Never commit keys.
